This article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring May 15, 2012, as Peace Officers Memorial Day and May 13 through May 19, 2012, as Police Week. The proclamation acknowledges the bravery and sacrifices of public safety officers who work to protect citizens and enforce laws. It emphasizes the importance of equipping law enforcement officers with the necessary tools and technology to ensure their safety and effectiveness. The proclamation also highlights the government's efforts to support the families of officers who have been injured or lost their lives in the line of duty. The President calls upon all Americans to observe these events with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and to fly the flag at half-staff on Peace Officers Memorial Day.